observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:

Cause the immediate refund of the amount paid to the beneficiaries who are not qualified to receive the grant by informing them through writing;

Upon receipt of the refunded amounts, cause the redistribution to identified eligible beneficiaries, if warranted or return the amount to the Bureau of Treasury;

We recommended that the LGU’s Appraisal and Disposal Committee observe the following measures:

Appraise the market value of the unserviceable properties and waste materials to be approved by COA;

Dispose the unserviceable properties and waste materials in accordance with the most appropriate mode of disposition of property as provided in Section 79 of RA No. 7160 which are either through, a) public auction; b) sale through negotiation; c) transfer without cost to other offices or department or any government agencies and; d) by destruction.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Require an explanation from the heads of offices on the absence in the APP or the Supplemental APP of the specific appropriation for the purchase of airline tickets;
Direct all department heads/end users to include in their Project Procurement Management Plan (PPMP) all acquisitions of airline tickets planned for the year and submit the same to the BAC Secretariat for consolidation and basis for preparation of the APP;
Ensure that no procurement shall be authorized and undertaken unless it is in accordance with an approved APP or supplemental APP; and
Instruct all officials and employees to purchase airline tickets directly from commercial airlines and service providers as provided under Section V, Item b of Annex H of the Revised IRR of RA No. 9184.

We recommended that Management:
Require the legislative branch to prepare an activity plan for the participation of its members to league seminars and activities to maximize resources and establish prioritization of attendance;
Encourage participation to seminars/conventions conducted within the province/region when these are conducted within the geographical area to lessen costs;
Direct municipal officials to ensure that payment of registration fees in attending seminars, trainings, assemblies and conferences sponsored by their respective leagues are supported with proper government official receipts;
Submit to the Audit Team a justification letter on the incurrence of unnecessary expenses relative to the two (2) regular employees and one (1) co-terminus employee who attended the PCL-Catanduanes Year End Assembly; and
Exercise due prudence in the disbursement of government funds to avoid incurrence of excessive expenditures.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) require the: 

1. DO to require the payees/beneficiaries to sign the payroll sheet as proof of receipt and submit it to the audit team, otherwise refund the amount of ₱88,434.20;

2. Municipal Accountant (MA) to prepare the necessary entries in the books to adjust/correct the errors committed in recording the advances for payroll.

We recommended that Management require the MAO and GSO to: 

Compare and reconcile their records and to correct/adjust whatever discrepancies; 

To include/account the properties recorded in the GL/SL but not included in the physical count as of December 31, 2021;   

To record in the book of accounts those properties found in the official station/office which are not recorded in the GL/SL, but included in the physical count and still owned by the agency;

To update and properly filled out the columns of the RPCPPE as to location, date of acquisition, accountable officers, serviceability, and nature/description PPEs;

To maintain subsidiary ledgers/PPELC and property cards for each PPE account; and



Conduct reconciliation of their records regularly/periodically to immediately notice and adjust if there are discrepancies/unreconciled items, in compliance with Section 53(b) of GAAM, Volume III.

