We recommended that the LCE direct the MT to: 
Require the RCs to remit immediately to the MT all unremitted collections in their custody;
Monitor strictly the remittances of collections made by RCs;
Ensure that the full amount collected by RCs are remitted intact; and
Require the RCs to remit their collections daily.

We recommended that the LCE require the MT to:
 Submit the subject DVs/payrolls/receipts and other supporting documents to the MAO;

Prepare the RCIs for all checks issued during the period and submit these to the MAO together with corresponding DVs;

Observe the ninety (90) day period within which to submit the unsubmitted DVs/payrolls/receipts before the suspensions mature into disallowance.

We recommended that Management:

Through the MSWD Officer conduct proper verification and validation of the targeted beneficiaries;
Ensure that the ESP and other similar benefits be granted only to duly qualified recipients observing the prohibitions stated in DSWD MC No. 09, Series of 2020;
Cause the immediate refund of the amount paid to the beneficiaries who are not qualified to receive the grant by informing them through writing;

Upon receipt of the refunded amounts, cause the redistribution to identified eligible beneficiaries, if warranted or return the amount to the Bureau of Treasury;
Through the MSWD to introduce more control and tools such as but not limited to:

Assign staff only to consolidate and deduplicate all target beneficiaries in Caramoran before uploading them to the DSWD FO;
Provide copies of written instructions on filling out the SAC forms with complete and accurate information to prevent duplication of entry in the master list when ran for deduplication.  Should the beneficiary is unable to write; the barangay council shall provide assistance;
Create simplified and summarized guidelines issued by the DSWD to be given to all PBs and urge them to reproduce more copies for their information campaign within their jurisdiction; and
Devise a tool or questionnaire-type device that will aid them during validation.

Through the Office of the Mayor and MSWD to:

a.  Urge all PBs to maintain close coordination and communication with their constituents to deter people from taking advantage of the weakness in the system;

b.	Encourage potential recipients to uphold guidelines to mitigate issues and avoid administrative cases that may be filed against them; and
c.	Request the cooperation and utmost support of all barangay officials to achieve a high success rate in implementing various programs of the LGU and the National Government.
Encourage various LGU offices to create a task force with their respective offices as members. Together with the assistance of all barangay officials and coordination with the Philippine Statistics Office, the task force will conduct an unannounced family profiling not tied to a specific program to mitigate the deliberate misrepresentation of any person and design a database that will contain the records and necessary information of families in the municipality of Caramoran. The national and local Government will use this system for implementation of future projects and derive benefits there from in various ways such as but not limited to:

List of all families requiring relief goods in times of crisis and state of calamity. The LGU can readily quantify the number of goods needed to be procured and speed up the distribution process;
Speed up the identification of targeted beneficiaries who require specific support from the government and maintain records of families who already received or constantly receiving assistance;

Deter individuals who want to take advantage of any program by deceiving any personnel attached to a government office;
Eliminate chances of double payment of assistance; and
Capture the actual population of the municipality, and the information gathered may be used for statistical and other legal purposes.

